Lemma LInt_p_dominated_convergence' {E : Set} {gen : (E → Prop) → Prop} {mu : measure gen} :
  ∀ f: nat → E → Rbar, ∀ g,
    (∀ n, non_neg (f n)) →
    (∀ n, measurable_fun_Rbar gen (f n)) →
    (∀ x, ex_lim_seq' (fun n ⇒ f n x)) →
     non_neg g → measurable_fun_Rbar gen g →
    (∀ n x, Rbar_le (f n x) (g x)) →
     is_finite (LInt_p mu g) →
    let lim_f := fun x ⇒ Lim_seq' (fun n ⇒ f n x) in
     measurable_fun_Rbar gen lim_f ∧
     is_finite (LInt_p mu lim_f) ∧
     LInt_p mu lim_f = Lim_seq' (fun n ⇒ LInt_p mu (f n)) ∧
     ex_lim_seq' (fun n ⇒ LInt_p mu (f n)).

Lemma is_LimSup_seq'_scal_l :
  ∀ u : nat → Rbar, ∀ a : R, 0%R ≤ a → ∀ l : R, is_LimSup_seq' u l →
    is_LimSup_seq' (fun n ⇒ Rbar_mult a (u n)) (Rbar_mult a l).

Section Boshner_integrable_fun.

    Context {X : Set}.
    Context {E : NormedModule R_AbsRing}.
    Context {gen : (X → Prop) → Prop}.
    Context {μ : measure gen}.

    Open Scope fun_scope.

    Record Bif {f : X → E} := mk_Bif {
        seq : nat → simpl_fun E gen;

        ax_notempty : inhabited X;
        ax_int : (∀ n : nat, integrable_sf μ (seq n));
        ax_lim_pw : (∀ x : X, is_lim_seq (fun n ⇒ seq n x) (f x));
        ax_lim_l1 : is_LimSup_seq' (fun n ⇒ LInt_p μ (‖ f - (seq n) ‖)%fn) 0
    }.

    Definition fun_Bif {f} (_ : @Bif f) := f.
    Coercion fun_Bif : Bif >-> Funclass.

End Boshner_integrable_fun.


Notation "'𝓛¹(' X ',' μ ',' E ')'" := { f : X → E | Bif μ f }
    (format "'[ ' '𝓛¹(' X ',' μ ',' E ')' ']'").

Section Bi_fun_prop.

    Context {X : Set}.
    Context {E : NormedModule R_AbsRing}.
    Context {gen : (X → Prop) → Prop}.
    Context {μ : measure gen}.

    Lemma measurable_Bif {f : X → E} :
        ∀ bf : Bif μ f, measurable_fun gen open bf.

    Lemma integrable_Bif {f : X → E} :
        ∀ bf : Bif μ f, is_finite (LInt_p μ (‖ bf ‖)%fn).

    Lemma Cauchy_seq_approx :
        ∀ f : X → E, ∀ s : nat → simpl_fun E gen, (∀ n : nat, integrable_sf μ (s n)) → inhabited X →
            (∀ x : X, is_lim_seq (fun n ⇒ s n x) (f x)) → is_LimSup_seq' (fun n ⇒ LInt_p μ (‖ f - (s n) ‖)%fn) 0
            → NM_Cauchy_seq (fun n ⇒ BInt_sf μ (s n)).

End Bi_fun_prop.

Delimit Scope Bif_scope with Bif.

Section Bif_sf.

    Context {X : Set}.
    Context (ι : inhabited X).
    Context {E : CompleteNormedModule R_AbsRing}.
    Context {gen : (X → Prop) → Prop}.
    Context {μ : measure gen}.

    Definition Bif_integrable_sf {s : simpl_fun E gen} :
        integrable_sf μ s → Bif μ s.
    Defined.

    Lemma Bif_integrable_sf_fun {s : simpl_fun E gen}
        {Hinteg : integrable_sf μ s} :
        ∀ x : X, Bif_integrable_sf Hinteg x = s x.

    Definition Bif_zero := Bif_integrable_sf (integrable_sf_zero _ μ).

    Lemma Bif_zero_fun :
        ∀ x : X, Bif_zero x = zero.

End Bif_sf.

Section Bif_op.

    Context {X : Set}.
    Context {E : CompleteNormedModule R_AbsRing}.
    Context {gen : (X → Prop) → Prop}.
    Context {μ : measure gen}.

    Definition Bif_plus {f g : X → E} (bf : Bif μ f) (bg : Bif μ g) :
        Bif μ (f + g)%fn.
    Defined.

    Lemma Bif_fn_plus {f g : X → E} (bf : Bif μ f) (bg : Bif μ g) :
        ∀ x : X, Bif_plus bf bg x = (bf x + bg x)%hy.

    Definition Bif_scal {f : X → E} (a : R_AbsRing) (bf : Bif μ f) : Bif μ (a ⋅ f)%fn.
    Defined.

    Lemma Bif_fn_scal {f : X → E} (a : R_AbsRing) (bf : Bif μ f) :
        ∀ x : X, Bif_scal a bf x = a ⋅ (bf x).

    Definition Bif_norm {f : X → E} (bf : Bif μ f) : Bif μ (‖f‖)%fn.
    Defined.

    Lemma Bif_fn_norm {f : X → E} (bf : Bif μ f) :
        ∀ x : X, Bif_norm bf x = ‖ bf x ‖.

End Bif_op.

Notation "bf + bg" := (Bif_plus bf bg) : Bif_scope.
Notation "a ⋅ bf" := (Bif_scal a bf) : Bif_scope.
Notation "‖ bf ‖" := (Bif_norm bf) : Bif_scope.
Notation "- bf" := (Bif_scal (opp one) bf) : Bif_scope.
Notation "bf - bg" := (bf + (- bg))%Bif : Bif_scope.

Definition inRange
    {X : Set} {A : AbsRing} {E : NormedModule A}
    (g : X → E) : E → Prop :=
        fun y ⇒ ∃ x : X, g x = y.

Lemma iRR {X : Set} {A : AbsRing} {E : NormedModule A}
    : ∀ g : X → E, ∀ x : X, inRange g (g x).

Module Bif_adapted_seq.

    Section construction_of_seq.

        Context {X : Set}.
        Context {E : CompleteNormedModule R_AbsRing}.
        Context {gen : (X → Prop) → Prop}.
        Context {μ : measure gen}.
        Context (ι : inhabited X).
        Context {f : X → E}.
        Context (Hmeas : measurable_fun gen open f).

        Context {u : nat → E}.
        Context (Hsep : NM_seq_separable_weak u (inRange f)).

        Context (Hinteg : is_finite (LInt_p μ (‖f‖)%fn)).

        Definition v (k : nat) : E :=
            match k with
                | O ⇒ zero
                | S k' ⇒ u k'
            end.

        Definition B (m : nat) (j : nat) :=
            ball_norm (v j) (/ (INR m + 1)).

        Definition A (n : nat) (m : nat) := fun x ⇒
            ∃ j : nat, (j < n)%nat ∧ B m j x.

        Lemma measB : ∀ m j, measurable open (B m j).

        Lemma measA : ∀ n m, measurable open (A n m).

        Lemma decB (m j : nat) (x : E) :
            {B m j x} + {¬ B m j x}.

        Close Scope R_scope.

        Lemma LPO_min_finite :
            ∀ m : nat, ∀ P : nat → Prop,
                (∀ j : nat, (j < m) → {P j} + {¬ P j})
                → { j : nat
                        | (j < m)
                        ∧ P j
                        ∧ (∀ i : nat, (i < j) → ¬ P i)
                    }
                    +
                    { ∀ j : nat, (j < m) → ¬ P j }.

        Lemma LPO_min_finite_decr :
            ∀ m : nat, ∀ P : nat → Prop,
                (∀ j : nat, (j < m) → {P j} + {¬ P j})
                → { j : nat
                        | (j < m)
                        ∧ P j
                        ∧ (∀ i : nat, (i > j) → (i < m) → ¬ P i)
                    }
                    +
                    { ∀ j : nat, (j < m) → ¬ P j }.

        Lemma decA (n m : nat) (x : E) :
            {A n m x} + {¬ A n m x}.

        Lemma decA_aux (max m : nat) (x : E) : ∀ j : nat,
            (j < max) → {A m j x} + {¬ A m j x}.

        Definition biggestA (max : nat) (x : E) : nat :=
            match LPO_min_finite_decr max (fun m ⇒ A max m x) (decA_aux max max x) with
                | inleft e ⇒ proj1_sig e
                | inright _ ⇒ max
            end.

        Lemma biggestA_le_max (max : nat) (x : E) :
            biggestA max x ≤ max.

        Lemma decB_aux (max : nat) (m : nat) (x : E) : ∀ j : nat,
            (j < max) → {B m j x} + {¬ B m j x}.

        Definition smallestB (max : nat) (m : nat) (x : E) : nat :=
            match LPO_min_finite max (fun j ⇒ B m j x) (decB_aux max m x) with
                | inleft e ⇒ proj1_sig e
                | inright _ ⇒ max
            end.

        Lemma smallestB_le_n (max : nat) (m : nat) (x : E) :
            m ≤ max → smallestB max m x = max ∨ smallestB max m x < max.

        Lemma smallestB_le_n_weak (max : nat) (m : nat) (x : E) :
            m ≤ max → smallestB max m x ≤ max.

        Definition whichn (n : nat) := fun x ⇒
            let m := biggestA n (f x) in
            if (m =? n) then n else
                smallestB n m (f x).

        Lemma whichn_le_n (n : nat) (x : X) :
            whichn n x ≤ n.

        Lemma biggestA_lt_max_spec (n : nat) (m : nat) : (m < n) →
            ∀ x : E,
            biggestA n x = m ↔ (A n m x ∧ (∀ j : nat, j > m → j < n → ¬ A n j x)).

        Lemma biggestA_eq_max_spec (n : nat) :
            ∀ x : E,
            biggestA n x = n ↔ (∀ j : nat, j < n → ¬ A n j x).

        Lemma smallestB_lt_max_spec (max : nat) (m : nat) (j : nat) : (j < max) →
            ∀ x : E,
            smallestB max m x = j ↔ (B m j x ∧ (∀ i : nat, i < j → ¬ B m i x)).

        Lemma smallestB_eq_max_spec (max : nat) (m : nat) :
            ∀ x : E,
            smallestB max m x = max ↔ (∀ j : nat, j < max → ¬ B m j x).

        Lemma whichn_spec_lt_n (n : nat) (j : nat) : (j < n) →
            ∀ x : X,
            whichn n x = j ↔
            ∃ m : nat, m < n ∧
            (
                (A n m (f x) ∧ ¬ (∃ k : nat, k > m ∧ k < n ∧ A n k (f x))) ∧
                (B m j (f x)) ∧ ¬ (∃ i : nat, i < j ∧ B m i (f x))
            ).

        Lemma whichn_spec_eq_n (n : nat) :
            ∀ x : X,
            whichn n x = n ↔ (¬ ∃ m : nat, m < n ∧ A n m (f x)).

        Open Scope R_scope.

        Definition valn (n : nat) : nat → E := fun k ⇒
            if (k <? n) then v k else zero.

        Lemma ax_val_max_which_n (n : nat) :
            valn n n = zero.

        Lemma ax_which_max_which_n (n : nat) :
            ∀ x : X, whichn n x ≤ n.

        Close Scope R_scope.

        Lemma ax_measurable_n (n : nat) :
            ∀ j : nat, j ≤ n
                → measurable gen (λ x : X, whichn n x = j).

        Definition s' (n : nat) : simpl_fun E gen :=
            mk_simpl_fun (whichn n) (valn n) n
            (ax_val_max_which_n n)
            (ax_which_max_which_n n)
            (ax_measurable_n n).

        Open Scope R_scope.

        Lemma le_s'n_two_f (n : nat) :
            ∀ x : X, ‖ s' n x ‖ ≤ 2 × ‖ f x ‖.

        Lemma s'_approx : ∀ x : X,
            ∀ m k : nat, B m k (f x)
                → ∀ n : nat, (m < n)%nat → (k < n)%nat →
                ball_norm (f x) (/ (INR m + 1)) (s' n x).

        Lemma s'_pointwise_cv :
            (∀ x : X, is_lim_seq (fun n ⇒ s' n x) (f x)).

        Definition s (n : nat) : simpl_fun E gen :=
            proj1_sig (sf_remove_zeros (s' n)).

        Lemma s'_s_ext (n : nat) : ∀ x : X,
            s' n x = s n x.

        Lemma s_nz (n : nat) :
            ∀ k : nat, (k < max_which (s n))%nat → val (s n) k ≠ zero.

        Lemma le_sn_two_f (n : nat) :
            ∀ x : X, ‖ s n x ‖ ≤ 2 × ‖ f x ‖.

        Lemma s_pointwise_cv :
            (∀ x : X, is_lim_seq (fun n ⇒ s n x) (f x)).

        Lemma s_integrable_sf : ∀ n : nat,
            integrable_sf μ (s n).

        Lemma s_l1_cv :
            (is_LimSup_seq' (fun n ⇒ LInt_p μ (‖ f - (s n) ‖)%fn) 0).

        Lemma Bif_separable_range : Bif μ f.

    End construction_of_seq.

End Bif_adapted_seq.

Export Bif_adapted_seq(Bif_separable_range).

Require Import Reals countable_sets Qreals.

Section R_valued_Bif.

    Context {X : Set}.
    Context {gen : (X → Prop) → Prop}.
    Context {μ : measure gen}.

    Lemma R_Bif {f : X → R_NormedModule} :
        measurable_fun gen open f →
        is_finite (LInt_p μ (‖f‖)%fn) →
        inhabited X →
            Bif μ f.

    Lemma R_bif_fun
        {f : X → R_NormedModule}
        {Hmeas : measurable_fun gen open f}
        {Hfin : is_finite (LInt_p μ (‖f‖)%fn)}
        {ι : inhabited X} :
        ∀ x : X, R_Bif Hmeas Hfin ι x = f x.

End R_valued_Bif.

Section strongly_measurable_fun.

    Context {X : Set}.
    Context {E : CompleteNormedModule R_AbsRing}.
    Context {gen : (X → Prop) → Prop}.
    Context {μ : measure gen}.

    Definition strongly_measurable f :=
        { s : nat → simpl_fun E gen
            | (∀ x : X, is_lim_seq (fun n ⇒ s n x) (f x))
        }.

    Lemma strongly_measurable_measurable {f : X → E} :
        strongly_measurable f → measurable_fun gen open f.

    Lemma strongly_measurable_plus {f g : X → E} :
        strongly_measurable f → strongly_measurable g
            → strongly_measurable (f + g)%fn.

    Lemma strongly_measurable_scal {f : X → E} :
        ∀ a : R, strongly_measurable f →
            strongly_measurable (a ⋅ f)%fn.

    Lemma strongly_measurable_opp {f : X → E} :
        strongly_measurable f → strongly_measurable (fun x ⇒ - (f x))%hy.

    Lemma strongly_measurable_minus {f g : X → E} :
        strongly_measurable f → strongly_measurable g
            → strongly_measurable (f - g)%fn.

    Lemma separable_Range_measurable_strongly_measurable {f : X → E} (u : nat → E) :
        (NM_seq_separable_weak u (inRange f)) → measurable_fun gen open f
            → strongly_measurable f.

    Lemma Bif_strongly_measurable {f : X → E} :
        Bif μ f → strongly_measurable f.

End strongly_measurable_fun.


Module strongly_measurable_separated_range_proof.

    Section seq_construction.

        Context {X : Set}.
        Context {E : CompleteNormedModule R_AbsRing}.
        Context {gen : (X → Prop) → Prop}.
        Context {μ : measure gen}.
        Context {f : X → E}.
        Context (Hsm : strongly_measurable gen f).

        Fixpoint u_aux (n : nat) : (E × nat × nat) :=
            match Hsm with exist s _ ⇒
                match n with
                    | O ⇒
                        (val (s O) O, O, O)
                    | S n' ⇒
                        let '(_, term, value) := u_aux n' in
                        if value =? max_which (s term) then
                            (val (s (S term)) O, S term, O)
                        else
                            (val (s term) (S value), term, S value)
                end
            end.

        Definition u : nat → E := fun n ⇒ fst (fst (u_aux n)).

        Lemma u_aux_spec :
            match Hsm with exist s _ ⇒
                ∀ n : nat, ∀ k : nat, k ≤ max_which (s n) →
                    ∃ m : nat, u_aux m = (val (s n) k, n, k)
            end.

        Lemma u_spec :
            match Hsm with exist s _ ⇒
                ∀ n : nat, ∀ k : nat, k ≤ max_which (s n) →
                    ∃ m : nat, u m = val (s n) k
            end.

        Lemma strongly_measurable_separated_range :
            NM_seq_separable_weak u (inRange f).

    End seq_construction.

End strongly_measurable_separated_range_proof.

Export strongly_measurable_separated_range_proof(strongly_measurable_separated_range).

Section Bif_characterisation.

    Context {X : Set}.
    Context {E : CompleteNormedModule R_AbsRing}.
    Context {gen : (X → Prop) → Prop}.
    Context {μ : measure gen}.

    Lemma strongly_measurable_integrable_Bif {f : X → E}
        : strongly_measurable gen f → is_finite (LInt_p μ (‖f‖)%fn)
            → inhabited X → Bif μ f.

    Lemma strongly_measurable_integrable_Bif_correct
        {f : X → E} {Hmeas : strongly_measurable gen f}
        {Hfin : is_finite (LInt_p μ (‖f‖)%fn)} {ι : inhabited X}
        : ∀ x : X, f x =
        strongly_measurable_integrable_Bif Hmeas Hfin ι x.

    Lemma strongly_measurable_lim_seq {limf : X → E} (f : nat → X → E) :
        (∀ n : nat, strongly_measurable gen (f n)) →
        (∀ x : X, is_lim_seq (fun n ⇒ f n x) (limf x)) →
            (strongly_measurable gen limf).

End Bif_characterisation.

Section BInt_def.

    Context {X : Set}.
    Context {E : CompleteNormedModule R_AbsRing}.
    Context {gen : (X → Prop) → Prop}.
    Context {μ : measure gen}.

    Definition BInt {f : X → E} (bf : Bif μ f) :=
        lim_seq (fun n ⇒ BInt_sf μ (seq bf n)).

    Theorem is_lim_seq_BInt {f : X → E} (bf : Bif μ f) :
        is_lim_seq (fun n ⇒ BInt_sf μ (seq bf n)) (BInt bf).

End BInt_def.

Notation "'∫B' bf" := (BInt bf)
        (only printing, at level 45, format "'[ ' '∫B' bf ']'") : Bif_scope.

Section BInt_prop.

    Context {X : Set}.
    Context {E : CompleteNormedModule R_AbsRing}.
    Context {gen : (X → Prop) → Prop}.
    Context {μ : measure gen}.

    Open Scope Bif_scope.

    Lemma BInt_ext {f f' : X → E} :
        ∀ bf : Bif μ f, ∀ bf' : Bif μ f', (∀ x : X, f x = f' x) →
            BInt bf = BInt bf'.

    Lemma BInt_BInt_sf {s : simpl_fun E gen} :
        ∀ π : integrable_sf μ s, ∀ ι : inhabited X,
        BInt_sf μ s = BInt (Bif_integrable_sf ι π).

End BInt_prop.

Section BInt_indic.

    Context {X : Set}.
    Context (ι : inhabited X).
    Context {E : CompleteNormedModule R_AbsRing}.
    Context {gen : (X → Prop) → Prop}.
    Context {μ : measure gen}.

    Lemma BInt_indic :
        ∀ P : X → Prop, ∀ π : measurable gen P, ∀ π' : is_finite (μ P),
            BInt (Bif_integrable_sf ι (integrable_sf_indic π π')) = μ P.

End BInt_indic.

Section BInt_op.

    Context {X : Set}.
    Context {E : CompleteNormedModule R_AbsRing}.
    Context {gen : (X → Prop) → Prop}.
    Context {μ : measure gen}.

    Open Scope hy_scope.
    Open Scope Bif_scope.

    Lemma BInt_plus {f g : X → E} :
        ∀ (bf : Bif μ f) (bg : Bif μ g),
            BInt (Bif_plus bf bg) = ((BInt bf) + (BInt bg))%hy.

    Lemma BInt_scal {f : X → E} :
        ∀ (bf : Bif μ f), ∀ (a : R_AbsRing),
            BInt (Bif_scal a bf) = (a ⋅ (BInt bf))%hy.

    Lemma norm_BInt_le {f : X → E} :
        ∀ (bf : Bif μ f),
            ‖ BInt bf ‖%hy ≤ BInt (‖bf‖)%Bif.

End BInt_op.

Section BInt_linearity.

    Context {X : Set}.
    Context {E : CompleteNormedModule R_AbsRing}.
    Context {gen : (X → Prop) → Prop}.
    Context {μ : measure gen}.

    Open Scope hy_scope.
    Open Scope Bif_scope.

    Lemma BInt_linearity {f g : X → E} :
        ∀ (bf : Bif μ f) (bg : Bif μ g), ∀ a b : R,
            BInt (a ⋅ bf + b ⋅ bg)
            = (a ⋅ (BInt bf) + (b ⋅ (BInt bg)))%hy.

    Lemma BInt_zero {f : X → E} :
        ∀ (bf : Bif μ f),
            (∀ x : X, bf x = zero) → BInt bf = zero.

    Lemma BInt_minus {f g : X → E} :
        ∀ bf : Bif μ f, ∀ bg : Bif μ g,
            BInt (bf - bg)%Bif = ((BInt bf) - (BInt bg))%hy.

    Lemma BInt_opp {f : X → E} :
        ∀ bf : Bif μ f,
            (BInt (- bf)) = (- (BInt bf))%hy.

End BInt_linearity.

Library BInt_LInt_p

From Coq Require Import

Section BInt_to_LInt_p.

    Context {X : Set}.
    Context {gen : (X → Prop) → Prop}.
    Context {μ : measure gen}.

    Lemma LInt_p_minus_le :
        ∀ f g : X → R,
        inhabited X →
        measurable_fun_R gen f →
        measurable_fun_R gen g →
        (∀ x : X, 0 ≤ f x) →
        (∀ x : X, 0 ≤ g x) →
        is_finite (LInt_p μ f) →
        is_finite (LInt_p μ g) →
            Rabs (LInt_p μ f - LInt_p μ g) ≤ LInt_p μ (fun x ⇒ Rabs (f x - g x)).

    Lemma is_finite_LInt_p_Bif {f : X → R} :
        ∀ bf : Bif μ f,
        (∀ x : X, 0 ≤ bf x) →
        is_finite (LInt_p μ (λ x : X, bf x)).

    Definition sf_shifter (sf : simpl_fun R_NormedModule gen) :
        simpl_fun R_NormedModule gen.
    Defined.

    Lemma pos_shifted_sf :
        ∀ sf : simpl_fun R_NormedModule gen,
            ∀ x : X, 0 ≤ (sf + (sf_shifter sf))%sf x.

    Lemma BInt_LInt_p_eq {f : X → R} :
        ∀ bf : Bif μ f,
        (∀ x : X, 0 ≤ bf x) →
        BInt bf = LInt_p μ (bf : X → R).

End BInt_to_LInt_p.

Section BInt_R_prop.

    Context {X : Set}.
    Context {gen : (X → Prop) → Prop}.
    Context {μ : measure gen}.

    Lemma BInt_Rplus {f g : X → R} :
        ∀ bf : Bif μ f, ∀ bg : Bif μ g,
        BInt (bf + bg)%Bif = BInt bf + BInt bg.

    Lemma BInt_Rscal {f : X → R} :
        ∀ bf : Bif μ f, ∀ a : R,
        BInt (a ⋅ bf)%Bif = a × BInt bf.

    Lemma BInt_Ropp {f : X → R} :
        ∀ bf : Bif μ f, ∀ a : R,
        BInt (- bf)%Bif = - BInt bf.

    Lemma BInt_Rminus {f g : X → R} :
        ∀ bf : Bif μ f, ∀ bg : Bif μ g,
        BInt (bf - bg)%Bif = BInt bf - BInt bg.

    Lemma BInt_Rlinearity {f g : X → R} :
        ∀ bf : Bif μ f, ∀ bg : Bif μ g, ∀ a b : R,
            BInt (a ⋅ bf + b ⋅ bg)%Bif
            = (a × (BInt bf) + (b × (BInt bg))).

    Lemma BInt_ge_0 {f : X → R} :
        ∀ bf : Bif μ f,
        (∀ x : X, 0 ≤ f x) →
            0 ≤ BInt bf.

    Lemma BInt_monotone {f g : X → R} :
        ∀ bf : Bif μ f, ∀ bg : Bif μ g,
        (∀ x : X, f x ≤ g x) → BInt bf ≤ BInt bg.

End BInt_R_prop.

Section BInt_dominated_convergence_proof.

    Context {X : Set}.
    Context {E : CompleteNormedModule R_AbsRing}.
    Context {gen : (X → Prop) → Prop}.
    Context {μ : measure gen}.

    Context {f : nat → X → E}.

    Theorem BInt_dominated_convergence :
        ∀ bf : ∀ n : nat, Bif μ (f n),
        ∀ limf : X → E,
        (∀ x : X, is_lim_seq (λ n, f n x) (limf x)) →
        ∀ g : X → R,
        (measurable_fun_R gen g) →
        (∀ n : nat, ∀ x : X, ‖ f n x ‖ ≤ g x) →
        (is_finite (LInt_p μ g)) →
            { blimf : Bif μ limf
                    | is_lim_seq (λ n, BInt (bf n)) (BInt blimf) }.

End BInt_dominated_convergence_proof.

Section BInt_for_sf.

    Context {X : Set}.
    Context {E : NormedModule R_AbsRing}.
    Context {gen : (X → Prop) → Prop}.

    Open Scope R_scope.

    Definition BInt_sf (μ : measure gen) (sf : simpl_fun _ gen) : E :=
        sum_n
            (fun n ⇒ scal (real (μ (nth_carrier sf n))) (sf.(val) n))
            (sf.(max_which)).

End BInt_for_sf.

Notation "'∫B' sf 'd' μ" := (BInt_sf μ sf)
        (only printing, at level 45, format "'[ ' '∫B' sf 'd' μ ']'") : sf_scope.

Section BInt_sf_indic.

    Context {X : Set}.
    Context {gen : (X → Prop) → Prop}.
    Context {μ : measure gen}.

    Open Scope R_scope.
    Open Scope fun_scope.

    Lemma BInt_sf_indic (P : X → Prop) (π_meas : measurable gen P)
        : BInt_sf μ (sf_indic_aux gen P π_meas) = real (μ P).

End BInt_sf_indic.

Open Scope nat_scope.

Lemma sum_n_m_scal_r {A : Ring} {E : ModuleSpace A} :
    ∀ a : nat → A, ∀ u : E, ∀ n m : nat,
        sum_n_m (fun k : nat ⇒ scal (a k) u) n m = scal (sum_n_m (fun k : nat ⇒ (a k)) n m) u.

Lemma sum_n_scal_r {A : Ring} {E : ModuleSpace A} :
    ∀ a : nat → A, ∀ u : E, ∀ n m : nat,
        sum_n (fun k : nat ⇒ scal (a k) u) n = scal (sum_n (fun k : nat ⇒ (a k)) n) u.

Lemma sum_n_sum_Rbar :
    ∀ u : nat → Rbar, ∀ n : nat, (∀ k : nat, k ≤ n → is_finite (u k))
    → sum_n (fun k ⇒ real (u k)) n = real (sum_Rbar n u).

Section BInt_sf_plus.

    Context {X : Set}.
    Context {E : NormedModule R_AbsRing}.
    Context {gen : (X → Prop) → Prop}.
    Context {μ : measure gen}.

    Open Scope R_scope.
    Open Scope nat_scope.
    Open Scope sf_scope.

    Lemma BInt_sf_plus_aux {sf_f sf_g : simpl_fun E gen} :
        integrable_sf μ sf_f → integrable_sf μ sf_g →
            BInt_sf μ (sf_f + sf_g) = ((BInt_sf μ sf_f) + (BInt_sf μ sf_g))%hy.

End BInt_sf_plus.

Section BInt_sf_scal.

    Context {X : Set}.
    Context {E : NormedModule R_AbsRing}.
    Context {gen : (X → Prop) → Prop}.
    Context {μ : measure gen}.

    Open Scope R_scope.
    Open Scope nat_scope.
    Open Scope sf_scope.

    Lemma BInt_sf_scal_aux :
        ∀ a : R_AbsRing, ∀ sf : simpl_fun E gen,
            BInt_sf μ (a ⋅ sf) = (a ⋅ (BInt_sf μ sf))%hy.

End BInt_sf_scal.

Section BInt_sf_linearity.

    Context {X : Set}.
    Context {E : NormedModule R_AbsRing}.
    Context {gen : (X → Prop) → Prop}.
    Context {μ : measure gen}.

    Open Scope R_scope.
    Open Scope nat_scope.
    Open Scope sf_scope.

    Lemma BInt_sf_lin_aux {sf sg : simpl_fun E gen} :
        ∀ a b : R_AbsRing, integrable_sf μ sf → integrable_sf μ sg →
            BInt_sf μ (a ⋅ sf + b ⋅ sg)
            = ((a ⋅ (BInt_sf μ sf)) + (b ⋅ (BInt_sf μ sg)))%hy.

End BInt_sf_linearity.

Lemma norm_scal_eq {E : NormedModule R_AbsRing} :
    ∀ r : R, ∀ x : E, ‖ r ⋅ x ‖ = | r | ⋅ ‖ x ‖.

Section BInt_sf_norm.

    Context {X : Set}.
    Context {E : NormedModule R_AbsRing}.
    Context {gen : (X → Prop) → Prop}.
    Context {μ : measure gen}.

    Open Scope sf_scope.

    Lemma norm_Bint_sf_le :
        ∀ sf : simpl_fun E gen,
            (‖ BInt_sf μ sf ‖%hy ≤ BInt_sf μ (‖ sf ‖))%R.

End BInt_sf_norm.

Section BInt_well_defined.

    Context {X : Set}.
    Context {E : NormedModule R_AbsRing}.
    Context {gen : (X → Prop) → Prop}.
    Context {μ : measure gen}.

    Lemma BInt_sf_zero :
        ∀ sf : simpl_fun E gen,
            (∀ x : X, fun_sf sf x = zero)
            → BInt_sf μ sf = zero.

    Lemma BInt_sf_ext {sf sf' : simpl_fun E gen} :
        integrable_sf μ sf → integrable_sf μ sf' →
            (∀ x : X, fun_sf sf x = fun_sf sf' x) →
            BInt_sf μ sf = BInt_sf μ sf'.

End BInt_well_defined.

Lemma is_finite_sum_Rbar_map {T : Type} :
    ∀ l : list T, ∀ f : T → Rbar,
        (∀ a : T, In a l → is_finite (f a)) → is_finite (sum_Rbar_map l f).

Lemma sum_Rbar_map_Rbar_plus_finite {T : Type} :
    ∀ l : list T, ∀ f g : T → Rbar,
        (∀ a : T, In a l → is_finite (f a) ∧ is_finite (g a))
        → sum_Rbar_map l (fun a ⇒ Rbar_plus (f a) (g a))
            = Rplus (sum_Rbar_map l f) (sum_Rbar_map l g).

Lemma sum_Rbar_map_NoDup_NotIn {T : Type} :
    ∀ l : list T, ∀ f : T → Rbar, ∀ a : T,
        (∀ b : T, In b l → b ≠ a → f b = 0%R)
        → ¬ (In a l)
        → sum_Rbar_map l f = 0%R.

Lemma sum_Rbar_map_NoDup_In {T : Type} :
    ∀ l : list T, ∀ f : T → Rbar, ∀ a : T,
        (∀ b : T, In b l → b ≠ a → f b = 0%R)
        → NoDup l → In a l
        → sum_Rbar_map l f = f a.

Export Permutation.

Lemma sum_Rbar_Permutation :
    ∀ l l' : list R, Permutation l l'
        → ∀ f : R → Rbar,
        (∀ x : R, In x l → is_finite (f x))
        → sum_Rbar_map l f = sum_Rbar_map l' f.

Lemma sum_Rbar_map_sort :
    ∀ l : list R, ∀ f : R → Rbar, (∀ y : R, In y l → is_finite (f y)) →
        (sum_Rbar_map (sort_compl.sort Rle l) f) = (sum_Rbar_map l f).

Section Bochner_sf_Lebesgue_sf.

    Context {X : Set}.
    Context {gen : (X → Prop) → Prop}.
    Context {μ : measure gen}.

    Open Scope nat_scope.
    Open Scope list_scope.

    Lemma le_zero {n : nat} : n ≤ O → n = O.

    Lemma Bsf_to_Lsf_list_aux (sf : simpl_fun (R_NormedModule) gen) (n : nat)
    : { l : list R |
        (∀ x : X, sf.(which) x < n → List.In (sf x) l) ∧ (NoDup l)
        ∧ (integrable_sf μ sf → ( match n with O ⇒ zero | S n' ⇒ sum_n (λ k : nat, (real (μ (nth_carrier sf k))) ⋅ val sf k) n' end
            = sum_Rbar_map l
            ( λ y : R, Rbar_mult y (μ (λ x : X, sf x = y ∧ sf.(which) x < n)) ) ) ) }.

    Lemma Bsf_to_Lsf_list (sf : simpl_fun (R_NormedModule) gen)
    : { l : list R |
        (finite_vals_canonic sf l)
        ∧ (integrable_sf μ sf → sum_n (λ n : nat, (real (μ (nth_carrier sf n)) ⋅ val sf n)) (max_which sf) = sum_Rbar_map l
            (λ x : R, Rbar_mult x (μ (λ x0 : X, sf x0 = x)))) }.

    Definition is_SF_Bsf (sf : simpl_fun (R_NormedModule) gen) : SF gen sf.
    Defined.

    Lemma BInt_sf_LInt_SFp {sf : simpl_fun R_NormedModule gen} :
        integrable_sf μ sf → BInt_sf μ sf = LInt_SFp μ sf (is_SF_Bsf sf).

    Lemma Finite_BInt_sf_LInt_SFp {sf : simpl_fun R_NormedModule gen} :
        integrable_sf μ sf → Finite (BInt_sf μ sf) = LInt_SFp μ sf (is_SF_Bsf sf).

End Bochner_sf_Lebesgue_sf.


Section simpl_fun_integrability.

    Context {X : Set}.
    Context {A : AbsRing}.
    Context {E : NormedModule A}.
    Context {gen : (X → Prop) → Prop}.
    Context {μ : measure gen}.

    Lemma integrable_sf_finite_LInt_p :
        ∀ sf : simpl_fun E gen,
        integrable_sf μ sf → is_finite (LInt_SFp μ (‖sf‖)%sf (is_SF_Bsf μ (‖sf‖)%sf)).

    Lemma finite_LInt_p_integrable_sf :
        ∀ sf : simpl_fun E gen, inhabited X →
            (∀ k : nat, k < max_which sf → val sf k ≠ zero)
            → is_finite (LInt_SFp μ (‖sf‖)%sf (is_SF_Bsf μ (‖sf‖)%sf))
            → integrable_sf μ sf.

End simpl_fun_integrability.

Theorem normally_bounded_serie_is_convergent :

Library CUS_Lim_seq

From Coq Require Import

From Coquelicot Require Import

Section filterlim_complete_constr.

    Context {T : Type}.
    Context {U : CompleteSpace}.

    Lemma filterlim_locally_closely_correct :
        ∀ {F} {FF : ProperFilter F} (f : T → U),
            filterlim (fun x ⇒ (f (fst x), f (snd x))) (filter_prod F F) closely →
            filterlim f F (locally (lim (filtermap f F))).

    Lemma filterlim_locally_cauchy_correct :
        ∀ {F} {FF : ProperFilter F} (f : T → U),
            (∀ eps : posreal, ∃ P, F P ∧ ∀ u v : T, P u → P v → ball (f u) eps (f v)) →
            filterlim f F (locally (lim (filtermap f F))).

End filterlim_complete_constr.

Definition Cauchy_seq {S : UniformSpace} (u : nat → S) : Prop :=
    ∀ ɛ : R, ɛ > 0 → ∃ n : nat, ∀ p q : nat,
        p ≥ n → q ≥ n → ball (u p) ɛ (u q).

Section Cauchy_lim_seq_def.

    Context {S : CompleteSpace}.

    Definition lim_seq (u : nat → S) :=
        lim (filtermap u eventually).

    Lemma lim_seq_ext :
        ∀ u u' : nat → S,
            (∀ n : nat, u n = u' n) → ∀ l : S,
            filterlim u eventually (locally l) → filterlim u' eventually (locally l).

    Lemma filterlim_cauchy_seq_correct :
        ∀ u : nat → S,
            (∀ eps : posreal, ∃ P, eventually P ∧ ∀ p q : nat, P p → P q → ball (u p) eps (u q))
            → filterlim u eventually (locally (lim_seq u)).

    Lemma Cauchy_seq_eventually {u : nat → S} :
        Cauchy_seq u → (∀ eps : posreal, ∃ P, eventually P ∧ ∀ p q : nat, P p → P q → ball (u p) eps (u q)).

    Lemma is_filterlim_Cauchy_lim_seq :
        ∀ (u : nat → S), Cauchy_seq u →
            filterlim u eventually (locally (lim_seq u)).

End Cauchy_lim_seq_def.

Section lim_seq_prop.

    Context {S : UniformSpace}.
    Context {T : UniformSpace}.

    Lemma lim_seq_cte :
        ∀ s : S,
        filterlim (fun _ : nat ⇒ s) eventually (locally s).

    Lemma lim_seq_continuity :
        ∀ f : S → T, ∀ s : S,
        filterlim f (locally s) (locally (f s))
            → ∀ u : nat → S,
            filterlim u eventually (locally s) → filterlim (fun n ⇒ f (u n)) eventually (locally (f s)).

    Lemma lim_seq_pair :
        ∀ u : nat → S, ∀ v : nat → T, ∀ lu : S, ∀ lv : T,
            filterlim u eventually (locally lu) →
            filterlim v eventually (locally lv) →
            filterlim (fun n ⇒ (u n, v n)) eventually (filter_prod (locally lu) (locally lv)).

End lim_seq_prop.

Definition NM_Cauchy_seq {A : AbsRing} {E : NormedModule A} (u : nat → E) : Prop :=
    ∀ ɛ : R, ɛ > 0 → ∃ n : nat, ∀ p q : nat,
        p ≥ n → q ≥ n → ball_norm (u p) ɛ (u q).

Section NM_Cauchy_lim_seq_def.

    Context {A : AbsRing}.
    Context {E : CompleteNormedModule A}.

    Lemma NM_Cauchy_seq_Cauchy_seq :
        ∀ u : nat → E, NM_Cauchy_seq u → Cauchy_seq u.

    Lemma NM_Cauchy_seq_lim_seq_correct :
        ∀ (u : nat → E), ∀ (π : NM_Cauchy_seq u),
            is_lim_seq u (lim_seq u).

    Lemma NM_is_lim_seq_unique :
        ∀ u : nat → E, ∀ l l' : E,
            is_lim_seq u l → is_lim_seq u l' → l = l'.

    Lemma lim_seq_eq :
        ∀ u : nat → E, ∀ l : E,
            is_lim_seq u l → lim_seq u = l.

End NM_Cauchy_lim_seq_def.

Section NM_lim_seq_prop.

    Context {A : AbsRing}.
    Context {E : NormedModule A}.
    Open Scope hy_scope.
    Open Scope fun_scope.

    Lemma is_lim_seq_epsilon :
        ∀ u : nat → E, ∀ l : E,
            is_lim_seq u l ↔
            (∀ ɛ : R, 0 < ɛ → ∃ N : nat, ∀ n : nat, N ≤ n → (‖ minus (u n) l ‖%hy < ɛ)%R).

    Lemma lim_seq_plus :
        ∀ u v : nat → E, ∀ lu lv : E,
            is_lim_seq u lu → is_lim_seq v lv →
                is_lim_seq (u + v) (lu + lv)%hy.

    Lemma lim_seq_scal :
        ∀ a : nat → A, ∀ u : nat → E, ∀ la : A, ∀ lu : E,
            is_lim_seq a la → is_lim_seq u lu →
                is_lim_seq (fun n : nat ⇒ (a n) ⋅ (u n))%hy (la ⋅ lu)%hy.

    Lemma lim_seq_scal_r :
        ∀ a : A, ∀ u : nat → E, ∀ lu : E,
            is_lim_seq u lu →
                is_lim_seq (a ⋅ u) (a ⋅ lu)%hy.

    Lemma lim_seq_scal_l :
        ∀ a : nat → A, ∀ u : E, ∀ la : A,
            is_lim_seq a la →
                is_lim_seq (fun n ⇒ a n ⋅ u)%hy (la ⋅ u)%hy.

    Lemma lim_seq_opp :
        ∀ u : nat → E, ∀ lu : E,
            is_lim_seq u lu →
                is_lim_seq (fun n : nat ⇒ opp (u n)) (opp lu).

    Lemma lim_seq_mult :
        ∀ a b : nat → A, ∀ la lb : A,
        is_lim_seq a la → is_lim_seq b lb →
            is_lim_seq (fun n ⇒ (a n) × (b n)) (la × lb)%hy.

    Lemma lim_seq_norm :
        ∀ u : nat → E, ∀ lu : E,
        is_lim_seq u lu → is_lim_seq (‖ u ‖)%fn (‖ lu ‖)%hy.

    Lemma lim_seq_norm_zero :
        ∀ u : nat → E,
        is_lim_seq (‖u‖)%fn 0 → is_lim_seq u zero.

    Lemma lim_seq_bounded :
        ∀ u : nat → E,
            (∃ lu : E, is_lim_seq u lu)
            → { M : R | ∀ n : nat, (‖ u n ‖)%hy ≤ M }.

    Lemma measurable_fun_lim_seq {X : Set} {gen : (X → Prop) → Prop} :
        ∀ s : nat → X → E, (∀ n : nat, measurable_fun gen open (s n)) →
        ∀ f : X → E,
            (∀ x : X, is_lim_seq (fun n ⇒ s n x) (f x))
            → measurable_fun gen open f.

End NM_lim_seq_prop.

Section Rmax_n_def.

        match n return R with
            | O ⇒ u O

        end.

Definition is_lim_seq {A : AbsRing} {E : NormedModule A}
    (u : nat → E) (l : E) : Prop :=
        filterlim u eventually (locally l).

Definition convergent_seq {A : AbsRing} {E : NormedModule A}
    (u : nat → E) : Prop :=
        ∃ l : E, is_lim_seq u l.

Definition serie {A : AbsRing} {E : NormedModule A}
    (u : nat → E) : nat → E :=
        (fun n ⇒ sum_n u n) : nat → E.

Definition convergent_serie {A : AbsRing} {E : NormedModule A}
    (u : nat → E) : Prop :=
        convergent_seq (serie u).

Section normal_convergence.

    Open Scope R_scope.

    Definition upper_bounded_by (M : R) (u : nat → R) : Prop :=
        ∀ n : nat, (u n) ≤ M.

    Definition upper_bounded (u : nat → R) : Prop :=
        ∃ M : R, (upper_bounded_by M u).

    Definition normally_bounded_serie {A : AbsRing} {E : NormedModule A}
        (u : nat → E) : Prop :=
            upper_bounded (serie (fun n ⇒ norm (u n))).

    Definition normally_convergent_serie {A : AbsRing} {E : NormedModule A}
        (u : nat → E) : Prop :=
            ex_finite_lim_seq (serie (fun n ⇒ norm (u n))).

    Lemma normally_bounded_serie_is_normally_convergent_serie
        {A : AbsRing} {E : NormedModule A} :
            ∀ u : nat → E,
                normally_bounded_serie u → normally_convergent_serie u.

End normal_convergence.

Section simpl_fun_def.

    Context {X : Set}.
    Context {A : AbsRing}.
    Context {E : ModuleSpace A}.

    Definition indic (P : X → Prop) : X → A :=
        fun x ⇒
            match (excluded_middle_informative (P x)) return A with
                | left _ ⇒ one
                | right _ ⇒ zero
            end.

    Open Scope core_scope.
    Open Scope type_scope.
    Open Scope nat_scope.

    Context {gen : (X → Prop) → Prop}.
    Context (μ : measure gen).

    Record simpl_fun := mk_simpl_fun {
        which : X → nat;
        val : nat → E;
        max_which : nat;

        ax_val_max_which :
            val max_which = zero;
        ax_which_max_which :
            ∀ x : X, which x ≤ max_which;
        ax_measurable :
            ∀ n : nat, n ≤ max_which →
                measurable gen (fun x ⇒ which x = n);
    }.

    Definition integrable_sf (sf : simpl_fun) :=
        ∀ n : nat, n < max_which sf →
            is_finite (μ (fun x ⇒ which sf x = n)).

    Definition nth_carrier (sf : simpl_fun) (n : nat) : (X → Prop) :=
        (fun x ⇒ sf.(which) x = n).

    Definition fun_sf (sf : simpl_fun) : X → E :=
        fun x ⇒ sf.(val) (sf.(which) x).

    Coercion fun_sf : simpl_fun >-> Funclass.

    Definition is_simpl (f : X → E) :=
        ∃ sf : simpl_fun, ∀ x : X, sf x = f x.

End simpl_fun_def.


Notation "'χ(' P ')'" := (indic P) (at level 0) : fun_scope.

Section simpl_fun_indic.

    Context {X : Set}.
    Context (gen : (X → Prop) → Prop).

    Open Scope nat_scope.
    Open Scope R_scope.

    Definition sf_indic_aux (P : X → Prop) :
        measurable gen P → simpl_fun R_ModuleSpace gen.
    Defined.

    Lemma sf_indic :
        ∀ P : X → Prop, measurable gen P
            → is_simpl gen (χ(P): X → R).

    Context (μ : measure gen).

    Lemma integrable_sf_indic (P : X → Prop) (π : measurable gen P) :
        is_finite (μ P) → integrable_sf μ (sf_indic_aux P π).

End simpl_fun_indic.


Section sf_zero_fun.

    Context {X : Set}.
    Context (gen : (X → Prop) → Prop).

    Context {A : AbsRing}.
    Context {E : NormedModule A}.

    Definition sf_zero : simpl_fun E gen.
    Defined.

    Lemma sf_zero_zero : ∀ x : X, sf_zero x = zero.

    Context (μ : measure gen).

    Lemma integrable_sf_zero :
        integrable_sf μ sf_zero.

End sf_zero_fun.

Section simpl_fun_norm.

    Context {X : Set}.
    Context {A : AbsRing}.
    Context {E : NormedModule A}.
    Context {gen : (X → Prop) → Prop}.

    Open Scope R_scope.
    Open Scope nat_scope.

    Definition fun_norm (f : X → E) :=
        fun x ⇒ norm (f x).

    Notation "‖ f ‖" := (fun_norm f) (at level 100) : fun_scope.

    Definition sf_norm_aux (sf : simpl_fun E gen) : simpl_fun R_ModuleSpace gen.
    Defined.

    Context {μ : measure gen}.

    Lemma integrable_sf_norm {sf : simpl_fun E gen} (isf : integrable_sf μ sf) :
        integrable_sf μ (sf_norm_aux sf).

    Notation "‖ sf ‖" := (sf_norm_aux sf) (at level 100) : sf_scope.

    Lemma sf_norm :
        ∀ f : X → E, is_simpl gen f →
            is_simpl gen (fun_norm f).

    Lemma fun_sf_norm :
        ∀ sf : simpl_fun E gen,
            (∀ x : X, fun_sf (‖sf‖) x = (‖ fun_sf sf x ‖)%hy).

End simpl_fun_norm.

Notation "‖ f ‖" := (fun_norm f) (at level 100) : fun_scope.
Notation "‖ sf ‖" := (sf_norm_aux sf) (at level 100) : sf_scope.

Close Scope nat_scope.

Section simpl_fun_plus.

    Context {X : Set}.
    Context {A : AbsRing}.
    Context {E : NormedModule A}.
    Context {gen : (X → Prop) → Prop}.

    Open Scope nat_scope.

    Definition fun_plus (f : X → E) (g : X → E) :=
        (fun x ⇒ plus (f x) (g x)).

    Notation "f + g" := (fun_plus f g) (left associativity, at level 50) : fun_scope.

    Definition sf_plus_aux (sf sg : simpl_fun E gen) : simpl_fun E gen.
    Defined.

    Notation "sf + sg" := (sf_plus_aux sf sg) (left associativity, at level 50) : sf_scope.

    Lemma sf_plus :
        ∀ f g : X → E,
        is_simpl gen f → is_simpl gen g →
        is_simpl gen (fun_plus f g).

    Lemma fun_sf_plus :
        ∀ sf sg : simpl_fun E gen,
            (∀ x : X, fun_sf (sf + sg)%sf x = (fun_sf sf x + fun_sf sg x)%hy).

    Context {μ : measure gen}.

    Lemma integrable_sf_plus {sf sg : simpl_fun E gen} :
        (integrable_sf μ sf) → (integrable_sf μ sg) → (integrable_sf μ (sf_plus_aux sf sg)).

End simpl_fun_plus.

Notation "f + g" := (fun_plus f g) (left associativity, at level 50) : fun_scope.
Notation "sf + sg" := (sf_plus_aux sf sg) (left associativity, at level 50) : sf_scope.

Section simpl_fun_scal.

    Context {X : Set}.
    Context {A : AbsRing}.
    Context {E : NormedModule A}.
    Context {gen : (X → Prop) → Prop}.

    Open Scope nat_scope.

    Definition fun_scal (a : A) (g : X → E) :=
        (fun x ⇒ scal a (g x)).

    Notation "a ⋅ g" := (fun_scal a g) (left associativity, at level 45) : fun_scope.

    Definition sf_scal_aux (a : A) (sf : simpl_fun E gen) : simpl_fun E gen.
    Defined.

    Notation "a ⋅ sf" := (sf_scal_aux a sf) (left associativity, at level 45) : sf_scope.

    Lemma sf_scal :
        ∀ a : A, ∀ f : X → E,
        is_simpl gen f →
        is_simpl gen (fun_scal a f).

    Lemma fun_sf_scal :
        ∀ a : A, ∀ sf : simpl_fun E gen,
            (∀ x : X, fun_sf (a ⋅ sf) x = (a ⋅ (fun_sf sf x))%hy).

    Context {μ : measure gen}.

    Lemma integrable_sf_scal (a : A) {sf : simpl_fun E gen} :
        integrable_sf μ sf → integrable_sf μ (sf_scal_aux a sf).

End simpl_fun_scal.

Notation "a ⋅ g" := (fun_scal a g) (left associativity, at level 45) : fun_scope.
Notation "a ⋅ sf" := (sf_scal_aux a sf) (left associativity, at level 45) : sf_scope.
Notation "- g" := (fun_scal (opp one) g) : fun_scope.
Notation "- sg" := (sf_scal_aux (opp one) sg) : sf_scope.
Notation "f - g" := (fun_plus f (- g))%fn : fun_scope.
Notation "sf - sg" := (sf_plus_aux sf (- sg)) : sf_scope.

Section simpl_fun_bounded.

    Context {X : Set}.
    Context {A : AbsRing}.
    Context {E : NormedModule A}.
    Context {gen : (X → Prop) → Prop}.
    Context {μ : measure gen}.

    Open Scope hy_scope.

    Definition sf_bounded :
        ∀ sf : simpl_fun E gen, { M : R | ∀ x : X, ‖ fun_sf sf x ‖ ≤ M }.
    Qed.

End simpl_fun_bounded.

Lemma finite_sum_Rbar :
    ∀ u : nat → Rbar, ∀ n : nat, (∀ k : nat, k ≤ n → is_finite (u k))
    → is_finite (sum_Rbar n u).

Section simpl_fun_meas.

    Context {X : Set}.
    Context {A : AbsRing}.
    Context {E : NormedModule A}.
    Context {gen : (X → Prop) → Prop}.
    Context {μ : measure gen}.

    Lemma measurable_sf_preim :
        ∀ sf : simpl_fun E gen, ∀ y : E,
            measurable gen (fun x : X ⇒ sf x = y).

    Lemma sf_measurable_preim_le :
        ∀ sf : simpl_fun E gen, ∀ n : nat, n ≤ max_which sf →
            measurable gen (λ x : X, which sf x ≤ n).

    Lemma sf_measurable_preim_lt :
        ∀ sf : simpl_fun E gen, ∀ n : nat, n ≤ max_which sf →
            measurable gen (λ x : X, which sf x < n).

    Lemma is_finite_sf_preim_lt {sf : simpl_fun E gen} :
        integrable_sf μ sf → ∀ n : nat, n ≤ max_which sf →
            is_finite (μ (λ x : X, which sf x < n)).

    Lemma sf_decomp_preim_which :
        ∀ sf : simpl_fun E gen, ∀ y : E,
            (μ (fun x : X ⇒ sf x = y))
            = sum_Rbar (max_which sf) (fun k ⇒ (μ (fun x : X ⇒ val sf k = y ∧ which sf x = k))).

    Lemma finite_sf_preim_neq_0 {sf : simpl_fun E gen} :
        integrable_sf μ sf → ∀ y : E, y ≠ zero →
            is_finite (μ (fun x : X ⇒ sf x = y)).

    Lemma measurable_fun_sf_aux :
        ∀ sf : simpl_fun E gen,
            (∀ P : E → Prop, measurable open P → measurable gen (fun x : X ⇒ P (sf x))).

    Lemma measurable_fun_sf :
        ∀ sf : simpl_fun E gen,
            measurable_fun gen open sf.

    Lemma finite_sf_preim_neq_0' {sf : simpl_fun E gen} :
        integrable_sf μ sf →
            is_finite (μ (fun x : X ⇒ sf x ≠ zero)).

End simpl_fun_meas.

Section simpl_fun_nonzero.

    Context {X : Set}.
    Context {A : AbsRing}.
    Context {E : NormedModule A}.
    Context {gen : (X → Prop) → Prop}.

    Lemma sf_nonzero_ind (sf : simpl_fun E gen) (n : nat) :
        { sf' : simpl_fun E gen
                | (∀ x : X, sf x = sf' x)
                ∧ (max_which sf' ≤ max_which sf)
                ∧ ((max_which sf - max_which sf') ≤ n)
                ∧ (∀ k : nat, k < n - (max_which sf - max_which sf') → k < max_which sf' → val sf' k ≠ zero)
        }.

    Lemma sf_remove_zeros (sf : simpl_fun E gen) :
        { sf' : simpl_fun E gen
                | (∀ x : X, sf x = sf' x)
                ∧ (∀ k : nat, k < max_which sf' → val sf' k ≠ zero)
        }.

End simpl_fun_nonzero.

Library square_bij

From Coq Require Import
    ssreflect
    ssrsearch
    Arith
    Lia
    Utf8
.

Section square_bij_def.

    Context (n : nat).

    Definition square_bij :=
        fun c : (nat × nat) ⇒
        let (k1, k2) := c in
        k1 × n + k2.

    Definition square_bij_inv :=
        fun m : nat ⇒
            ((m / n), (m mod n)).

End square_bij_def.

Section square_bij_prop.

    Context (n : nat).

    Lemma is_bij_square :
        ∀ k1 k2 : nat, k2 ≤ n → square_bij_inv (S n) (square_bij (S n) (k1, k2)) = (k1, k2).

    Lemma confined_snd_square_inv :
        ∀ m : nat, (snd (square_bij_inv (S n) m)) ≤ n.

    Lemma is_bij_square_inv :
        ∀ m : nat, square_bij (S n) (square_bij_inv (S n) m) = m.

    Lemma square_bij_corner :
        ∀ n' : nat,
            square_bij (S n) (n', n) = ((S n') × (S n) - 1).

    Lemma square_bij_inv_corner :
        ∀ n' : nat,
            square_bij_inv (S n) ((S n') × (S n) - 1) = (n', n).

    Lemma confined_square_inv : ∀ n' : nat,
        ∀ m : nat, m ≤ S n' × S n - 1 →
            let (k1, k2) := square_bij_inv (S n) m in
            k1 ≤ n' ∧ k2 ≤ n.

    Lemma confined_square : ∀ n' : nat,
        ∀ k1 k2 : nat,
            k1 ≤ n' ∧ k2 ≤ n → square_bij (S n) (k1, k2) ≤ (S n' × S n) - 1.

End square_bij_prop.

From Coquelicot Require Import
    Hierarchy
.

Section square_bij_sum.

    Lemma sum_n_m_shift {G : AbelianGroup} :
        ∀ n m k : nat, ∀ u : nat → G,
            sum_n_m (fun x ⇒ u (k + x)) n m
            = sum_n_m u (k + n) (k + m).

    Lemma square_bij_sum {G : AbelianGroup} :
        ∀ n1 n2 : nat, ∀ u : nat → G,
            sum_n u (S n1 × S n2 - 1) =
            sum_n (
                fun k1 ⇒ sum_n (
                    fun k2 ⇒ u (square_bij (S n2) (k1, k2))
                ) n2
            ) n1.

End square_bij_sum.

Section open_subspaces.

    Context {S : UniformSpace}.

    Lemma open_union {I : Type} :
        ∀ U : I → (S → Prop), (∀ i : I, open (U i))
            → open (fun x ⇒ ∃ i : I, U i x).

    Context {A : AbsRing}.
    Context {E : NormedModule A}.
    Open Scope hy_scope.

    Lemma NM_open_ball_norm : ∀ (a : E) (ɛ : R), 0 < ɛ → open (ball_norm a ɛ).

    Lemma NM_open_neq : ∀ x : E,
        open (fun y ⇒ y ≠ x).

End open_subspaces.

Section closed_subspaces.

    Context {S : UniformSpace}.

    Lemma closed_inter {I : Type} :
        ∀ F : I → (S → Prop), (∀ i : I, closed (F i))
            → closed (fun x ⇒ ∀ i : I, F i x).

End closed_subspaces.

Section density.

    Context {S : UniformSpace}.

    Definition fun_dense (P : S → Prop) (Q : S → Prop) (f : ∀ x : S, Q x → posreal → S) : Prop :=
        (∀ x : S, P x → Q x) ∧
        (∀ x : S, ∀ π : Q x,
            ∀ ɛ : posreal, ball x ɛ (f x π ɛ) ∧ P (f x π ɛ)).

    Definition dense (P : S → Prop) (Q : S → Prop) : Prop :=
        ∃ f, fun_dense P Q f.

    Lemma fun_dense_dense {P Q : S → Prop} {f : ∀ x : S, Q x → posreal → S} :
        fun_dense P Q f → dense P Q.

    Definition fun_separable (u : nat → S) (P : S → Prop) (f : ∀ x : S, P x → posreal → nat) : Prop :=
        (∀ n : nat, P (u n)) ∧
        (∀ x : S, ∀ π : P x,
            ∀ ɛ : posreal, ball x ɛ (u (f x π ɛ))).

    Definition separable (P : S → Prop) : Prop :=
        ∃ u : nat → S, (∀ n : nat, P (u n)) ∧ ∀ x : S, P x →
            ∀ ɛ : posreal, ∃ n : nat, ball x ɛ (u n).

    Lemma fun_separable_separable {u : nat → S} {P : S → Prop} {f : (∀ x : S, P x → posreal → nat)} :
        fun_separable u P f → separable P.

    Definition seq_separable (u : nat → S) (P : S → Prop) : Prop :=
        (∀ n : nat, P (u n)) ∧
        (∀ x : S, P x →
            ∀ ɛ : posreal, ∃ n : nat, ball x ɛ (u n)).

    Lemma fun_separble_seq_separable {u : nat → S} {P : S → Prop} {f} :
        fun_separable u P f → seq_separable u P.

End density.

Section denseQR.

    Definition QinR (x : R) :=
        ∃ r : Q, x = Q2R r.

    Definition denseQR_fn : ∀ x : R_UniformSpace, True → posreal → R_UniformSpace :=
        fun x _ sigɛ ⇒ Q2R
            match sigɛ with mkposreal ɛ _ ⇒
                let q := up (/ɛ) in
                (Qmake (up (x×IZR q)) (Z.to_pos q))
            end.

    Theorem fun_denseQR : fun_dense QinR (fun _ : R_UniformSpace ⇒ True) denseQR_fn.

    Definition separableR_fn : ∀ x : R_UniformSpace, True → posreal → nat :=
        fun x π sigɛ ⇒ bij_QN
            match sigɛ with mkposreal ɛ _ ⇒
                let q := up (/ɛ) in
                (Qmake (up (x×IZR q)) (Z.to_pos q))
            end.

    Theorem fun_separableR : fun_separable (fun n ⇒ Q2R (bij_NQ n)) (fun _ ⇒ True) separableR_fn.

    Theorem separableR : separable (fun _ : R_UniformSpace ⇒ True).

    Theorem seq_separableR : seq_separable (fun n ⇒ Q2R (bij_NQ n)) (fun _ : R_UniformSpace ⇒ True).

End denseQR.

Section NM_density.

    Context {A : AbsRing}.
    Context {E : NormedModule A}.

    Definition NM_separable (P : E → Prop) : Prop :=
        ∃ u : nat → E, ∀ x : E, P x →
            ∀ ɛ : posreal, ∃ n : nat, ball_norm x ɛ (u n).

    Lemma separable_NM_separable :
        ∀ P : E → Prop, separable P → NM_separable P.

    Definition NM_seq_separable (u : nat → E) (P : E → Prop) : Prop :=
        (∀ n : nat, P (u n)) ∧
        (∀ x : E, P x →
            ∀ ɛ : posreal, ∃ n : nat, ball_norm x ɛ (u n)).

    Lemma seq_separable_NM_seq_separable {u : nat → E} {P : E → Prop} :
        seq_separable u P → NM_seq_separable u P.

    Definition dist (x : E) (P : E → Prop) :=
        (Glb_Rbar (fun d : R ⇒ ∃ y : E, P y ∧ ‖ minus x y ‖ = d)).

    Definition NM_seq_separable_weak (u : nat → E) (P : E → Prop) : Prop :=
        (∀ x : E, P x →
            ∀ ɛ : posreal, ∃ n : nat, ball_norm x ɛ (u n)).

    Lemma NM_seq_separable_seq_separable_weak {u : nat → E} {P : E → Prop} :
        NM_seq_separable u P → NM_seq_separable_weak u P.

    Lemma NM_seq_separable_weak_le {u : nat → E} {P : E → Prop} :
        ∀ Q : E → Prop,
            (∀ x : E, Q x → P x) →
            NM_seq_separable_weak u P →
            NM_seq_separable_weak u Q.

End NM_density.

Section NM_seq_separable_subspace.


End NM_seq_separable_subspace.

Lemma NM_separableR : NM_separable (fun _ : R_NormedModule ⇒ True).

Lemma NM_seq_separableR : NM_seq_separable (fun n ⇒ Q2R (bij_NQ n)) (fun _ : R_NormedModule ⇒ True).

Lemma NM_seq_separable_weakR : NM_seq_separable_weak (fun n ⇒ Q2R (bij_NQ n)) (fun _ : R_NormedModule ⇒ True).
